Step 1: Download AWS CLI v2 installer
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

⭐ Step 2: Unzip installer
sudo apt install unzip -y
unzip awscliv2.zip

⭐ Step 3: Install AWS CLI
sudo ./aws/install

⭐ Step 4: Verify installation
aws --version


You should see:

aws-cli/2.x.x Python/3.x Linux/...

FIX: Set up AWS Credentials on Ubuntu

You must configure AWS CLI first.

Run:

aws configure


It will ask you for:

AWS Access Key ID: 
AWS Secret Access Key:
Default region name:
Default output format:
